Former Nasdaq Managing Director Johnson Sentenced to 42 Months in Prison

-- B y   S a r a   F o r d e n
-- 
2011-08-12T14:13:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/former-nasdaq-managing-director-johnson-sentenced-to-42-months-in-prison.html
Former Nasdaq Stock Market Managing
Director  Donald Johnson  was sentenced to 42 months in prison for
using information obtained from his position with the exchange
to engage in insider trading.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sara Forden in Washington at 
 sforden@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
